</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[113,647,887,991]" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">
CONSERVATION STATUS. — According to reports of the CITES Division of the DFC 
<collectingCountry box="[393,445,914,938]" name="Togo" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">Togo</collectingCountry>
, 50 live specimens of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[210,321,940,964]" class="Reptilia" family="Lamprophiidae" genus="Lamprophis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="18" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[210,321,940,964]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">Lamprophis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were exported from 
<collectingCountry box="[517,567,940,964]" name="Togo" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">Togo</collectingCountry>
in 2001 and 2002 but the precise species was not stated.
